# ripgrep config file

# ripgrep supports configuration files. Set RIPGREP_CONFIG_PATH to a
# configuration file. The file can specify one shell argument per line. Lines
# starting with '#' are ignored. For more details, see the man page or the
# README.

##
## See https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/blob/master/GUIDE.md
##

# Because who cares about case!?
--smart-case

# Don't let ripgrep vomit really long lines to my terminal, and show a preview.
--max-columns=500
# ripgrep 0.9.0 doesn't support this flag
# Comment it out until all servers have been updated.
# openSUSE Leap 15.2 has ripgrep 0.8.1
--max-columns-preview

# Don't respect ignore files
# More often than not, I'm searching for files in the ignore list.
--no-ignore
